al_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Docs page(s)\n\nhttps://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/command-line-interface#--ext\r\nhttps://eslint.org/docs/next/use/migrate-to-9.0.0\r\nhttps://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/migration-guide#cli-flag-changes\n\n### What documentation issue do you want to solve?\n\nWhen running the 9.0.0 alpha 0 version of ESLint, I get:\r\n\r\n```\r\nInvalid option '--ext' - perhaps you meant '-c'?\r\nYou're using eslint.config.js, some command line flags are no longer available. Please see https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/command-line-interface for details.\r\n```\r\n\r\nVisiting the page states that `--ext` is `eslintrc Mode Only` but doesn't state how it has been replaced and what I have to do to make sure it still functions the same.\r\n\r\nThe main 9.0.0 migration page also doesn't list the change - though this [duplicate(?) page](https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/migration-guide#cli-flag-changes) lists it as being removed, but still doesn't specify the replacement.\n\n### What do you think is the correct solution?\n\nI think adding descriptions that indicate the files are now detected from the configuration, and that also points to https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/configuration-files-new\n\n### Participation\n\n- [ ] I am willing to submit a pull request for this change.\n\n### Additional comments\n\n_No response_","closed_by":{"login":"mdjermanovic","id":44349756,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0MzQ5NzU2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/44349756?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdjermanovic","html_url":"https://github.com/mdjermanovic","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdjermanovic/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdjermanovic/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdjermanovic/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdjermanovic/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptio